FBIS3-6282 "dreas051_m_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-051 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 Thailand New Association To Promote Contacts With Laos BK1403081794 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 GMT 14 Mar 94 BK1403081794 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Thai-Lao Association has been set up to promote people-to-people contact between the two countries. The association will conduct social, cultural, economic, and academic activities. The agreement on the revival of the association was reached recently during a meeting of the Thai-Lao Joint Commission on bilateral cooperation in Vientiane. According to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the head office of the Thai-Lao Association is located at the Department of Information, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, in Bangkok. Former Foreign Minister Asa Sarasin served as president of the association on the Thai side, while Mr. Khamphai Boupha served as the president of the association on the Lao side. Former Finance Minister Wiraphong Ramangkun served as the secretary general. The general public are invited to apply for membership of the association at the Department of Information.
